The paper describes a neural approach for converting whispered alaryngeal speech to fully-voiced speech, which involves speech enhancement and generative adversarial networks. This work is related to speech processing and synthesis, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, since the paper focuses on developing a speaker-dependent model, which is a specific application of speech processing, cs.SD is the most likely sub-category.
